# Protect main branch

Agents must **not** merge into, push to, or commit directly on `main` unless the user **explicitly** asks in the current message (e.g. "merge M0 to main", "commit on main").

## Default workflow

- Implement and fix on a feature or milestone branch (`feature/<id>-…`, `M0`, etc.).
- Open or update a PR from that branch; leave `main` unchanged.
- Only the user approves review and requests the merge to `main`.

## Forbidden without explicit instruction

- `git checkout main` then commit
- `git merge …` into `main`
- `git push origin main`
- Rewriting `main` (reset, rebase onto main, force-push)

## Allowed on any branch except main

- Commits, pushes, and PRs from feature/milestone branches
- Updating `docs/PROJECT.md` status on the active work branch

## If unsure

Stay on the current feature/milestone branch and ask before touching `main`.
